casebody.data:
No. 302,

Misc.

Shamery v. Illinois.

Appeal from the Supreme Court of Illinois.

Per Curiam:

The appeal is dismissed for want of jurisdiction. 28 U. S. C. *935§ 1257 (2). Treating the papers whereon the appeal was taken as a petition for writ of certiorari as required by 28 U. S. C. § 2103, certiorari is denied.
